===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|transliteratus}} past participle of {{m|la|transliterare||to transliterate}}, from {{m|la|trans-||across}} + {{m|la|littera||letter}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{label|en|linguistics|translation studies}} The act or product of [[transliterating]], or of representing [[letter]]s or [[word]]s in the [[character]]s of another [[alphabet]] or [[script]].
# {{label|en|sign language}} The act or product of rendering [[speech]] in [[sign language]], or vice versa.

